    <summary>An interface used to receive events generated by a <c><see cref="T:Javax.Sql.IPooledConnection" /></c>.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">An interface used to receive events generated by a <c><see cref="T:Javax.Sql.IPooledConnection" /></c>.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
 This interface would typically be implemented by a component which manages a
 connection pool (a connection pool manager). A connection triggers an event
 to a <c>ConnectionEventListener</c> either when the application closes a
 connection it has been using or when a significant error occurs while the
 connection is being used.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
 The connection pool manager can return closed connections to the pool for
 later reuse. Connections experiencing an error should be discarded.
</para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/javax/sql/ConnectionEventListener.html" target="_blank">[Android Documentation]</a>
        </format>
      </para>
    </remarks>
    <since version="Added in API level 1" />
  </Docs>
